==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} ''[[ladde]]''

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /læd/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æd|-æd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[boy]].
# A familiar term of address for a [[man]].
# A [[groom]] who works with [[horse]]s (also called ''[[stable-lad]]'').

====Usage notes====
Prevalent in Northern English dialects such as [[Geordie]] and [[Northumbrian]].

